Defendant Ryan C Willis in court with attorney Andrew J Shaw.  Timothy F. Westphal appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Plea Colloquy.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.    Penalty enhancer struck by Court upon motion of the State.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

60 days Jail.  (First 10 days Straight Time.  Remaining  time Huber WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.)  Credit - 1 day

Term of Probation: 12 months  Court would review petition to terminate probation after 10 months.  

